text: Kentawka Canal is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Variant names are "Kentawah Canal", "Kentawaha Creek" and "Kentawha Creek". Kentawka is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "place where beavers are brought forth in abundance". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Neshoba County, Mississippi
title: Kentawka Canal
